subject: I don‚Äôt normally do this but thought I would share this from my elderly neighbour who is not on next door‚Ä¶
body:
A man called ‚ÄúMichael K‚Äù is fraudulently advertising and selling Camden resident parking bays online (please see picture attached). This is happening in Clarence Gardens on the Regent‚Äôs Park Estate.  

Michael has instructed his customers to ‚Äúpark anywhere as we do not have allocated bays‚Äù. The resident parking bays are NOT his to sell they belong to residents who are paying for the spaces.

This is causing a great inconvenience for residents who are unable to park in their parking spaces including the elderly and disabled. Not to mention the unnecessary pollution and litter that these drivers are brining to our residential estate. 

Michael has used the address 4 Englefield NW1 3LN and the mobile number 07586209189 on his adverts and has had over 200 bookings. My neighbour has asked Michael to stop but he has refused. Camden Council estate parking rules state that you ‚Äúmust not under any circumstances sub-letting the parking spaces‚Äù.
